cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with optimizing the performance metrics of throughput and packet drop rate in a network coded TDD satellite system, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The use of random linear network coding (RLNC) and the optimization of transmission strategies can be related to information theory.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The optimization of system parameters and the interplay of different users with different packet erasure conditions can be related to systems and control.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The multi-user broadcast case and the optimization of system parameters can be related to distributed computing.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The consideration of delay sensitive applications can be related to multimedia.
